# GitFlow Configuration

## Branch Structure
- main: Production-ready code
- develop: Development branch
- feature/*: Feature branches
- release/*: Release preparation branches
- hotfix/*: Production fixes

## Branch Naming Conventions
- Feature branches: feature/description-of-feature
- Release branches: release/vX.Y.Z
- Hotfix branches: hotfix/description-of-fix

## Commit Message Format
<type>(<scope>): <description>

[optional body]

[optional footer(s)]

Types:
- feat: A new feature
- fix: A bug fix
- docs: Documentation changes
- style: Code style changes (formatting, etc.)
- refactor: Code changes that neither fix bugs nor add features
- perf: Performance improvements
- test: Adding or modifying tests
- chore: Changes to build process or auxiliary tools

## Merge Strategy
- Feature branches: Squash and merge into develop
- Release branches: Merge into main and develop
- Hotfix branches: Merge into main and develop

## Version Tags
- Format: vX.Y.Z (Semantic Versioning)
- Tag message should include release notes 